Aframomum corrorima

    Authority   (Host) P. Beauv
      Family    Liliopsida:Zingiberidae:Zingiberales:Zingiberaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2863

   Notes
   SOURCES (A. corrorima (Braun) Jansen)
   Jansen P 1981 pp 10-20 [LIG, RAIN, TEMP, USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial aromatic herb. The plant require 3 years to first harvest and
   have 7 years of economical life. The fruits are mature about 2-3 months
   after flowering.
   COMMON NAMES
   Korarima, Korarima cardamon, False cardamom, Guragi spice, Cardamome
   d'Ethiopie, Poivre d'Etiopie, Abyssinischen kardamon, Kwererima,
   Kewreriam, Corrorima, Oghio, Orsha, Ofio, Otiyo, Heil, Habhal-habashi.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: A. korarima. Korarima can be found in Ethiopia at
   elevations from (1350)-1700-2000 m. The plant can reach a height of 1-2
   m. In the wild korarima grows in almost the same habitats as coffee.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
